label: AL rdfs:label@en
definition: AL IAO:0000115@en

label: organismal
definition: Root node for organismal module.

label: biomaterial specimen
definition: A sample that is comprised predominately of living (or decomposing) material; for use when more specific information on composition of sample is not provided.

label: cell
definition: A material entity that has a plasma membrane and results from cellular division.

label: trophic class
definition: An organismal grouping baised on how a living entity acquires or generates food and energy from a living, dead, or non-living entity.
editors note: In ECOCORE these are direct subclasses to organism OBI:0100026, we could do that here if desired.

label: heterotroph
editors note: ECOCORE has more subclasses that could be imported.

label: mixotroph
definition: An organism that obtains carbon for growth and development by a combination of heterotrophy (metabolizing biogenic organic compounds derived from living or dead material ) and autotrophy (capable of incorporating inorganic carbon into its biomass).

label: informal classification
definition: The classification groups of biological organisms based on shared characteristics that are not part of a rigorous taxonomic framework.

label: plankton size
definition: Classification by planktonic size range.

label: Femtoplankton
definition: Plankton classification by size range: <0.2 um (viruses).

label: Picoplankton
definition: Plankton classification by size range: 0.2-2.0 um (bacteria, very small Eukaryotes).

label: Nanoplankton
definition: Plankton classification by size range: 2-20 um (diatoms, dinoflagellates, protozoa).

label: Microplankton
definition: Plankton classification by size range: 20-200 um (diatoms, dinoflagellates, protozoa, copepod nauplii, etc.).

label: Mesoplankton
definition: Plankton classification by size range: 0.2-20 mm (mostly zooplankton).

label: Macroplankton
definition: Plankton classification by size range: 2-20 cm.

label: plankton group
definition: Plankton classification by general functional group.

label: zooplankton
definition: Plankton consisting of small animals and the immature stages of larger animals.

label: phytoplankton
definition: Plankton consisting of small (mainly microscopic) photosynthetic organisms.

label: ciliate
definition: Plankton consisting of single-celled protozoa with cilia.

label: common name
definition: The natural language (non-taxonomic) name of the type of organism that is the subject of a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

label: fish
definition: A limbless cold-blooded vertebrate animal with gills and fins and living wholly in water.

label: diazotroph
definition: An organism capable of nitrogen fixation (conversion of atmospheric dinitrogen into bioavailable forms).

label: heterocyst-forming diazotroph
definition: An organism which uses heterocycts for nitrogen fixation (conversion of atmospheric dinitrogen into bioavailable forms).

label: taxonomy
definition: The classification groups of biological organisms based on shared characteristics.

label: taxonomic rank
definition: The relative level of a group of organisms in a taxonomic hierarchy.

label: domain
definition: A taxonomic rank which is the broadest unit of classification.

label: kingdom
definition: A taxonomic rank which is classified above phylum and below domain.

label: phylum
definition: A taxonomic rank which is classified above class and below kingdom.

label: class
definition: A taxonomic rank which is classified above order and below phylum.

label: order
definition: A taxonomic rank which is classified above family and below class.

label: family
definition: A taxonomic rank which is classified above genus and below order.

label: genus
definition: A taxonomic rank which is classified above species and below family.

label: species
definition: A taxonomic rank which is most basic or specific unit of classification.

label: WoRMS ID
definition: Taxonomic classification of organisms as described by unique identifiers within the World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS) taxonomic classification database.
editors note: Future direction to make OBO compliant IDs for WoRMS

label: NCBI taxonomy ID
definition: Taxonomic classification of organisms as described by unique identifiers within the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI) taxonomy database.
editors note: Cross listed in external repositories? Perhaps better to import relevant NCBITaxon subclasses and add them here.

label: taxonomic lineage
definition: The root of the combined NCBI and WoRMS taxonomic hierarchy.
